        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana: Fish Feed Plants of Production Capacity of at least 100 Ton/Day, introduced by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry &amp;amp; Dairying, Government of India, aims to provide capital subsidy for setting up fish feed plants with a minimum production capacity of 100 tons per day. The objective is to enhance the availability of high-quality and affordable feed for fish farmers, supporting the expansion of aquaculture in Haryana. This is a Centrally Sponsored Scheme, under which the project is jointly funded by the Central and State Governments: 50% of the subsidy amount is contributed by the Central Government, and 50% is provided by the State Government. Beneficiaries are expected to operate and maintain the plant independently and ensure the supply of feed to fishers at affordable prices.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- The project cost is ₹650,00,000/-\n\n> **Subsidy Distribution :**\n\n\n1. A 40% subsidy is available for the General Category.\n1. A 60% subsidy is offered for SC (Scheduled Caste) and Women beneficiaries.\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "This scheme provides capital subsidy for setting up fish feed plants with a minimum production capacity of 100 tons per day, under the Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana (PMMSY) to general , schedule caste and women beneficiaries .",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
